## Application Architecture

- **Framework**: Dash (Plotly) - Python web application
- **Port**: 8000
- **Entry Point**: dash_app.py
- **Dependencies**: Listed in requirements.txt

## Environment Variables Required

All environment variables are configured in app.yaml:

✅ DATABRICKS_HOST
✅ DATABRICKS_CLIENT_ID
✅ DATABRICKS_CLIENT_SECRET (secret reference)
✅ DATABRICKS_SQL_WAREHOUSE_PATH
✅ GENIE_SPACE_ID (secret reference)
✅ LAKEBASE_INSTANCE_NAME
✅ LAKEBASE_DB_NAME
✅ LAKEBASE_SCHEMA

## Data Sources

Unity Catalog Tables:
- lakehouse_inn_catalog.voc.open_issues_diagnosis
- lakehouse_inn_catalog.voc.review_aspect_details
- lakehouse_inn_catalog.voc.hotel_locations

Lakebase OLTP:
- voc.aspect_runbook_db

## Security Considerations

✅ Uses OAuth M2M (service principal) authentication
✅ Secrets stored in Databricks Secrets
✅ No hardcoded credentials in code
✅ Environment-based configuration

## Features Verified for Deployment

✅ HQ Dashboard with tabbed interface
   - Tab 1: Property Analytics Dashboard
   - Tab 2: Aspect Analysis + Review Deep Dive
   - Tab 3: Generate Email
   - Floating Ask Genie section

✅ Property Manager Dashboard
✅ Executive KPIs
✅ Interactive US Map
✅ Regional Performance Analytics
✅ Email Generation with Runbook Integration
✅ Genie AI Integration
✅ Placeholder data fallback for offline mode

## Testing Before Deployment

Run locally to verify:
```bash
python dash_app.py
```

Then access: http://localhost:8000

## Deploy Command

```bash
databricks apps deploy
```

